description_en:
Core Effects
1. Promote Rooting and Strong Seedlings: Rapid root formation, developed root system, improved nutrient absorption efficiency, reduced occurrence of stunted and weak seedlings, leaves become dark green and thick, increased chlorophyll content, enhanced photosynthesis;
2. Enhance Stress Resistance: Strengthen resistance to low temperature and drought, reduce the incidence of seedling-stage damping-off and wilt;
3. Improve Quality and Increase Yield: Accelerate differentiation and heart leaf formation, bulbs become firm and uniform, reduce hollow and cracked bulbs.
Target Crops: Chinese cabbage, cabbage

Core Effects
1. Promote Root Growth and Seedling Vigor: Contains trace elements to rapidly promote root development and dense fibrous roots in scallions, ginger, and garlic, enhancing root absorption of water and nutrients, solving issues of slow seedling recovery after transplanting, seedling death, and root rot;
2. Enhance Stress Resistance: Strengthens plant resistance to cold, drought, waterlogging, and /pests and diseases, reducing damage from high temperature seedling burn, low temperature frost damage, and continuous cropping obstacles that cause weak growth, [SYMPTOM] yellowing leaves, and tip drying;
3. Improve Quality and Increase Yield: Promotes thick scallion stalks, full garlic bulbs, and large ginger rhizomes, reducing inferior qualities such as hollow stems, cracked bulbs, small cloves, and deformities.
Target Crops: Scallion, Ginger, Garlic

Core Effects
1. Rapid Greening: Nutrients can quickly penetrate the leaf cuticle, resolving yellowing, small leaves, leaf curling, and thin leaves caused by nutrient deficiency, phytotoxicity, or low temperature, making crop small leaves larger, leaf curling relaxed, and diseased leaves recover health and greenness;
2. Enhance Photosynthesis, Improve Quality and Yield: Increase chlorophyll content and photosynthetic efficiency, promote uniform fruit swelling, bright coloring, and increased hardness, reduce malformed fruit, fruit cracking, and physiological fruit drop;
3. Promote Root Growth and Seedling Vigor, Enhance Stress Resistance: Activate root vitality, promote new root germination; enhance plant resistance to drought, cold, saline-alkali, and pests and diseases; quickly alleviate growth disorders caused by phytotoxicity, fertilizer damage, high/low temperature stress, helping crops rapidly recover growth momentum.
Control Crops: Field crops (wheat, corn, rice, etc.), fruit trees (apple, pear, peach, citrus, etc.), vegetables (tomato, cucumber, chili, eggplant, etc.), flowers and seedlings (rose, succulent, pothos, etc.).
Additional Effects (from combined entries): Promote root growth and plant robustness: stimulate root cell division, enhance stem toughness, improve seedling vigor, reduce lodging.

Core Effects
1. Strengthen roots and stabilize seedlings, enhance stress resistance: Reinforce root cell walls, promote lateral root germination, reduce root rot and seedling death; ensure chlorophyll synthesis, leaves become dark green and thick, improve photosynthetic efficiency; overall enhance plant resistance to cold, drought, and diseases;
2. Promote flowering and fruit retention, prevent deformity and cracking: Supplement key micro and trace nutrients during flowering and fruit setting stages, extend pollination period, increase fruit set rate, reduce flower and fruit drop; balance growth rates of fruit skin and flesh, effectively prevent common eggplant deformity, cracking, stunted fruit, and green tip fruit;
3. Fruit enlargement and quality improvement: Promote uniform fruit enlargement, fruit skin becomes glossy black, fruit shape straight; improve flesh firmness and taste;
4. Prevent nutrient deficiency: Target physiological problems such as eggplant nutrient deficiency, avoid [SYMPTOM] leaf curling, chlorosis, growth stagnation, and other adverse symptoms.
Control crops: Eggplant

Core Effects
1. Nutritional Supply: Contains trace elements, suitable for direct absorption by hydroponic roots, preventing nutrient deficiency yellowing, small leaves, and stunted seedlings;
2. Root Promotion and Strengthening: Accelerates white root germination, making roots white, tender, and strong; inhibits harmful bacteria and green algae in water, purifies water quality, reduces black roots, root rot, and unpleasant odors;
3. Quality Improvement and Yield Increase, Promotes Flowering and Leaf Brightness: Leaves are dark green and glossy, flowers are large and colorful, flowering period is extended; enhances hydroponic crop stress resistance (high temperature, hypoxia), suitable for foliage plants, flowering plants, and fresh cut flower preservation.
Target Crops: Hydroponic vegetables (lettuce, romaine lettuce, etc.), foliage hydroponics (Epipremnum aureum, Dracaena sanderiana, spider plant, etc.), flowering hydroponics (water lily, hyacinth, narcissus, etc.).

Core Effects
1. Promote greening and strengthen leaves: Quickly repair physiological [SYMPTOM] yellowing leaves, small leaves, leaf curling, and leaf drop; thicken leaves; increase chlorophyll content; enhance photosynthesis;
2. Root growth and stress resistance: Promote white root germination and developed root systems; enhance drought, cold, phytotoxicity / frost damage resistance; reduce continuous cropping obstacles and premature aging;
3. Improve quality and increase yield: Protect flowers and fruits; promote fruit enlargement and coloring; improve fruit flavor.
Control crops: Field crops (wheat, corn, rice, etc.), fruit trees (apple, pear, peach, citrus, etc.), melons and fruits (watermelon, melon, etc.).

Core Effects
1. Promote flowering, optimize flower buds: Initiate flower bud differentiation early, increase the proportion of female flowers and the number of effective flowers; make flower buds full and flowering period uniform, reduce malformed flowers and aborted flowers; significantly improve flower bud development disorders caused by low temperature and insufficient light;
2. Preserve flowers and fruits, increase fruit set rate: Enhance pollen vitality and pollen tube elongation, improve the success rate of natural and artificial pollination; inhibit abscisic acid synthesis, reduce flower drop during flowering and fruit drop during young fruit stage;
3. Enhance stress resistance, promote fruit enlargement and quality improvement: Improve crop resistance to low temperature, drought, and flowering period diseases; accelerate cell division and enlargement of young fruits, promote directional nutrient transport to fruits; ensure uniform fruit size, bright color, reduce malformed and cracked fruits.
Target Crops: Fruit trees (apple, cherry, lychee, strawberry, etc.), melons and fruits (watermelon, cucumber, pumpkin, loofah, etc.), vegetables (tomato, chili, eggplant, cowpea, etc.), economic crops (cotton, rapeseed, etc.), flowers (honeysuckle, rose, etc.).
